Sentencas: Polarization characteristics of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells, fabricated by pulsed laser deposition and suspension plasma spray, were investigated.
Titulo: Polarization analysis for metal-supported SOFCs from different fabrication processes

Sentencas: With the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy and current-voltage polarization curves, the metal-supported SOFCs were compared and analyzed in terms of their cathode exchange current density, polarization loss and maximum power density over the temperature range of 400-600 degrees C.
Titulo: Polarization analysis for metal-supported SOFCs from different fabrication processes

Sentencas: The electrochemical mechanism for the linear polarization characteristics observed from the experimental data was addressed.
Titulo: Polarization analysis for metal-supported SOFCs from different fabrication processes

Sentencas: Results from experiments and simulation indicate that fabrication processes and operation temperatures play an important role in the electrochemical mechanism for linear polarization characteristics of metal-supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Polarization analysis for metal-supported SOFCs from different fabrication processes
